  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhanced protection of IDP Children and Women in camps (Jalozai and Togh Sarrai) and off-camp host communities (Hangu) through life-saving and time-critical assistance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">3.	Continuation of community based child protection mechanisms
a.	Members of 22 Child Protection Committees play effective roles in monitoring vulnerable children and women and linking them with referral services; 
b.	Community based protection mechanisms continue to access 87,968 children through extended outreach interventions and monitor their situation to benefit from life-saving and time-critical benefits, opportunities and services;
c.	Social protection schemes have child sensitive criteria and all eligible  children have received benefits from such schemes; 

****NCE request received on 21 Dec 2012- approved by USG on 24 Dec 2012 and extended until 31 Mar 2013</narrative>
  </description>
